{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peDismissal', 'text' : 'He who rose from the dead,'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peVE|Stichera01|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 2.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peVE|Stichera01|melody', 'text' : 'Joseph took You down.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peVE|Stichera01|text', 'text' : 'Christ, in Your compassion You appeared * in the flesh on earth, without leaving the Father's bosom on high. * Willingly You underwent Your holy Passion and death. * On the third day rose indeed; * and then, as almighty, * You entered and stood inside, although the doors were locked. * Then when Thomas touched Your divine rib, * he was filled with joy, and he called You * his Lord and Creator, glorifying You.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peVE|Stichera02|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 2.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peVE|Stichera02|melody', 'text' : 'Joseph took You down.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peVE|Stichera02|text', 'text' : 'With nails You were fixed onto the Cross; * then You tasted gall, O my Savior. Your side was pierced with a spear. * Undergoing death, O Christ, You were entombed as one dead; * and as God, You shattered the bonds of Hades, O Master, * resurrecting with yourself the dead of bygone times. * Then to prove Your own resurrection, * You entered the room without breaking * the locks on the doors where Your disciples were.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peVE|Stichera03|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 2.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peVE|Stichera03|melody', 'text' : 'Joseph took You down.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peVE|Stichera03|text', 'text' : 'Pascha is the present sacred feast, * mystical, divine holy Pascha, * this saving Passover, * Pascha that transports us to immortal life with God, * holy Pascha that takes away dejection and sorrow, * Pascha that gave joyous grace to the disciples of Christ. * Thomas then cried out to the Savior, * "You despoiled the kingdom of Hades; * my Lord and my God are You undoubtedly."'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peVE|SticGlory|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peVE|SticGlory|melody', 'text' : 'Idiomelon.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peVE|SticGlory|text', 'text' : 'What a paradoxical miracle! Unbelief produced certain faith. For when Thomas said, "If I do not see, I will not believe," and touched the Lord's side, then he theologized about the Incarnate One, and recognized that He was both the Son of God and also the One who had suffered in the flesh. He proclaimed the risen God, and he shouted in a loud voice, "My Lord and my God, glory to You!"'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peVE|Aposticha1|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peVE|Aposticha1|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peVE|Aposticha1|text', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peVE|Aposticha2|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peVE|Aposticha2|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peVE|Aposticha2|text', 'text' : 'The most melodious harp of the Apostles, set in motion by the Holy Spirit, abolished the rites of the odious demons; and by preaching faith in the only Lord, it redeemed the nations from the delusion of the idols, and taught them to worship the consubstantial Trinity.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peVE|Aposticha3|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peVE|Aposticha3|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peVE|Aposticha3|text', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peVE|AposGlory|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peVE|AposGlory|melody', 'text' : 'Idiomelon.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peVE|AposGlory|text', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Kathisma11|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Kathisma11|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Kathisma11|text', 'text' : 'When You the Life of the universe were nailed unto the Cross, * and You were reckoned among the dead, O Lord, the Immortal One, * O Savior, on the third day You arose, * and resurrected Adam from decay. * For this reason were the powers of heaven crying out to You, O Life-giver: * Glory to Your sufferings, O Christ; * glory to Your Resurrection; * glory to Your condescension, only One who loves mankind.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Kathisma12|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Kathisma12|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Kathisma12|text', 'text' : 'O wise fishermen of the civilized world, from God you received a compassionate heart, and thus you intercede on behalf of us who cry out: "Lord, save Your people and Your city, and free our souls from the woes that beset us, by the prayers of Your Apostles."'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Kathisma13|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Kathisma13|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Kathisma13|text', 'text' : 'Let all of us beseech the holy Martyrs of Christ God. * To Him they ever pray for our salvation and safety. * So let us all go to them, and approach them with ardent faith. * They pour out the grace of cures and healings profusely. * They defeat the hosts of evil spirits and demons, * as guardians of the Faith.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Kathisma1T|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Kathisma1T|melody', 'text' : 'The soldiers keeping watch.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Kathisma1T|text', 'text' : 'The Prophets openly prophesied and pronounced you * the Mother of our God; and the holy Apostles * declared this throughout the world; and for our part we have believed. * Therefore one and all, in truly Orthodox manner, * honor and extol you, blessed Maiden, and call you * Theotokos literally.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Kathisma21|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Kathisma21|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Kathisma21|text', 'text' : '"Since You have seen my side and the punctures the nails made, * no longer disbelieve in My rising, O Thomas," * the Lord said when He appeared to His Disciples ineffably, * after He had risen from the tomb on the third day. * Then the Twin believed and cried aloud to the Creator, * "My Lord and my God are You."'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds1|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds1|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds1|text', 'text' : 'We glorify Your divine condescension, and we sing Your praise, O Christ. You were born of a Virgin, and from the Father You remained inseparable. You suffered as a man and voluntarily endured the Cross. As one emerging from a bridal chamber, You rose from the sepulcher, in order to save the world. Glory to You, O Lord.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds2|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds2|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds2|text', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds3|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds3|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds3|text', 'text' : 'Greatly rejoice in the Lord, O Martyrs, for you fought the good fight, you stood up to emperors, and you were victorious over tyrants. You were not frightened by fire and sword. As wild beasts devoured your bodies, and you joined the Angels in sending up your hymns of praise to Christ, from heaven you received the crowns. Pray now that peace be granted to the world and great mercy to our souls.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|LaudsGlory|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|LaudsGlory|melody', 'text' : 'Idiomelon.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|LaudsGlory|text', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Aposticha1|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 2.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Aposticha1|melody', 'text' : 'O House of Ephratha. '}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Aposticha1|text', 'text' : 'Far from us now be gone * dejection of the passions * and thoughts that swirl like tempests, * and thus the sacred springtime of faith in Christ will blossom forth.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Aposticha2|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 2.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Aposticha2|melody', 'text' : 'O House of Ephratha. '}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Aposticha2|text', 'text' : 'Savior, You then appeared * to Your divine Apostles, although the doors were locked shut, * through them today renewing the Holy Spirit in our souls.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Aposticha3|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 2.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Aposticha3|melody', 'text' : 'O House of Ephratha. '}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|Aposticha3|text', 'text' : 'Seeing You, King of all, * now not with eyes, but rather * by heartfelt love and longing, * in hymns we magnify You, for we believe that You are God.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|AposGlory|mode', 'text' : 'Mode pl. 2.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|AposGlory|melody', 'text' : 'Idiomelon.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d082_en_US_dedes|peMA|AposGlory|text', 'text' : 'Eight days after Your resurrection, O King Jesus, the only-begotten Logos of the Father, You appeared to Your disciples, the doors being shut. You gave them Your peace, and You showed the marks of the nails to the unbelieving disciple. "Come and touch my hands and my feet, and my immaculate side." And he was convinced and cried to You, "My Lord and my God, glory to You!"'}
